Basic idea of the two-hand Post-Mechanical keyboard was formed in 2006. That idea was expanded to embrace Dvorak for European
languages. Creating a paradigmatic two-handed keyboard occasioned an innate obligation to render options for single-hand
typists. My reponsibility for the development of single-hand Dvorak versions was pragmatic.

A two-handed TKL version of the keyboard (sans case) was actualized by Troy Fletcher in 2023. He also designed a reversible
Left- and Right-Hand dual-use PCB. I used two of those those PCBs to make the right- and left-hand TKL prototypes.

